Craster's wives022236nooetr95zwvmfevde5rz0fcd9t5zfc91790242015-03-24T14:18:18ZThe Dragon Demands5014364{{Quote|He marries his daughters, and they give him more daughters, and on and on it goes.|[[Eddison Tollett]] explains where Craster gets his many wives.|What is Dead May Never Die}}
'''Craster's wives''' are a group of about a dozen women married to the [[Free Folk|wildling]] [[Craster]] and who dwell with him in his [[Craster's Keep|homestead]] in the [[Haunted Forest]]. Some (if not all) of Craster's wives are also his own daughters, which he &quot;marries&quot; once they have [[Flowering|flowered]]. Boys born from these couplings are sacrificed by Craster to the [[White Walkers]], while daughters are kept to serve him and marry him once they are of age - to produce more daughters to marry.  

This extreme [[Incest|incest]] is abhorrent to the [[Night's Watch]] as well as other wildling, and is not remotely tolerable in wildling culture.  Still, because he is one of the few homesteaders willing to give news and shelter to scouts of the Night's Watch, they grudgingly do not openly decry his behavior.
